        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 1:48PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Cass, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Dutton...                         Red Star...
Pettigrew...                      St. Paul...
Redding...                        Taft...
Brashears...                      Boston...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
